      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 1735: The new pre-lock `isUsable()` / `convModule()` path reads account configuration state before `configurationMutex_` is held. `doRegister()` previously made the usability decision under the mutex; moving part of it outside can race with concurrent enable/disable or active-state changes, and may create/load the conversation module using a stale `isEnabled()` value. Snapshot the required state under `configurationMutex_`, release it before loading conversations, then reacquire and revalidate before continuing.\n```suggestion\n    bool shouldLoadConversations \u003d false;\n    {\n        std::lock_guard lock(configurationMutex_);\n        shouldLoadConversations \u003d autoLoadConversations_ \u0026\u0026 isUsable();\n    }\n    if (shouldLoadConversations)\n        if (auto* cm \u003d convModule())\n            cm-\u003eloadConversationsIfNeeded();\n\n    std::lock_guard lock(configurationMutex_);\n```",
