      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 2577: `convModule()` now uses `isEnabled()` while constructing the module, but this method can be called from different contexts and not all callers necessarily hold `configurationMutex_`. If `isEnabled()` reads mutable account configuration, this introduces an unsynchronized read and makes the initial auto-load decision nondeterministic. Prefer passing an already-synchronized value from the caller that owns the account state, or document/enforce that `convModule()` is only called with the configuration lock held when the module can be created.\n```suggestion\n            autoLoadConversations_ \u0026\u0026 isEnabled()); // only if caller holds configurationMutex_\n```",
